	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxGuard" value="Member of the Terrax Guard"/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxGuardDescription" value="Improved morale. Has reduced ranged attacks if adjacent to a Shaken ally, moreso if adjacent to a Broken ally."/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxGuardFlavor" value="On Terrax, the Schola Excubitos trains all planetary forces. In essence, every Guardsman in the Terrax Guard is trained, equipped, and held to the same standards as Tempestus Scions and Commissars. Even the lowest Guardsman is elite, and they carry this with pride. Most flaunted is their discipline, and they hold their peers to these impossible standards. Even in the midst of battle, fleeing troops will find that the Terrax Guard can swiftly turn their weapons on cowards. Cowardice is an affront to Terrax honour, and the thought of letting it go unpunished is unbearable. The Commissariat has given its blessing for these executions, as it can be handy to have an entire regiment of commissars on call."/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxDiscipline" value="Terrax Discipline"/>
	<!-- <entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxDisciplineDescription" value="Adjacent allies gain increased accuracy and lose less morale."/> -->
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxDisciplineFlavor" value="Being assigned to operate with what is effectively a regiment of commissars is simultaneous inspiring and (much more so) terrifying. Guardsmen find themselves standing straighter and training more often, lest they risk being made an example of. It was bad enough with one pair of eyes, and now there's an entire platoon watching your every move."/>
