	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxOvercharged" value="Overcharged Weapon"/>
	<!-- <entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxOverchargedDescription" value=""/> -->
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxOverchargedFlavor" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/TerraxOverchargePlasmaFlavor'/>"/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxThrownPistol" value="Pistol Thrown"/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxThrownPistolDescription" value="Ranged weapon is unavailable."/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxThrownPistolFlavor" value="An overloaded plasma pistol's explosion will turn its wielder into a bubbling puddle of flesh. Throwing the weapon away can save the user's life, and it can even take the enemy's. However, guardsmen will have trouble explaining to the commissar why they decided that their life was worth more than a rare, meticulously crafted weapon. Many troopers find themselves handed over to the Adeptus Mechanicus for sentencing, and of those who can still feel, few remain satisfied with the decision they made on the battlefield."/>
	<!-- Terrax Colonel -->
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxColonelDiscipline" value="Colonel's Gaze"/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxColonelDisciplineDescription" value="Infantry gain increased accuracy and lose less morale. Members of the Terrax Guard gain increased ranged attacks and further increased melee attacks."/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxColonelDisciplineFlavor" value="Terrax Colonels lead the best of the best, necessitating the most effective methods. Common soldiers feel fear when seeing the Terrax Guard, but are somewhat inspired. Terrax Colonels know how to mitigate that fear without removing it completely. Balance is maintained between fear and a desire to act with initiative in order to impress their leader."/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxKillOrBeKilled" value="Kill or Be Killed"/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxKillOrBeKilledDescription" value="Unit gains increased ranged attacks, further increased melee attacks, and increased armour penetration. Upon killing an enemy, remove the health drain. Members of the Terrax Guard take more damage."/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxKillOrBeKilledFlavor" value="Terrax Colonels need to have exceptional motivational skills to lead the leaders. Weakness cannot be shown, and any undermining of authority must be quashed swiftly and harshly. The simplest solution is an execution, but ironically, overuse of such undermines confidence in the Colonel. Consequently, Terrax Colonels must eliminate up-and-coming competition in more subtle ways. Men cannot refuse the honour of leading the charge, as refusing would be treason and failing is punished the same way. However, subtlety can backfire. Being sent to a certain death makes men fight with increased ferocity, and this tenacity may truly bring glory. In the end, all is as the Emperor wills."/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxKillOrBeKilledDrain" value="Marked for Execution"/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxKillOrBeKilledDrainDescription" value="Lose health every turn"/>
	<entry name="AstraMilitarum/TerraxKillOrBeKilledDrainFlavor" value="&quot;Lads, redouble your efforts! The Colonel is almost finished reloading!&quot;"/>
</language>
